01:41:35,540 --> 01:41:39,780
But the point, and this is a big point, and it's another one of those miraculous points

1489
01:41:39,780 --> 01:41:46,340
that is very, very important, is that you can do these independent symmetry transformations

1490
01:41:46,340 --> 01:41:51,700
at different points, but only if you introduce a new field that lets you keep track of the

1491
01:41:51,700 --> 01:41:55,700
information relating what's going on at different points.

1492
01:41:55,800 --> 01:42:01,160
So these symmetries that can happen independently at every different point are called gauge

1493
01:42:01,160 --> 01:42:06,520
symmetries, or simply local symmetries in contrast with the global symmetries that

1494
01:42:06,520 --> 01:42:07,880
we were talking about.

